oc:kn_27c7c4fd a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing gradual RxJava-to-coroutines migration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Add kotlinx-coroutines-core and kotlinx-coroutines-rx3 (or rx2) as dependencies for gradual migration; bridge library provides asFlow() and asObservable() for interop at module boundaries." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without bridge libraries, module boundaries between RxJava and coroutines code cannot interoperate during incremental migration." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2fdeecda a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting subscribeOn/observeOn threading operators" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Place flowOn() at the end of the chain (it affects all upstream operators); it is analogous to subscribeOn, not observeOn. Collection always runs on the caller's dispatcher." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Misplacing flowOn() breaks threading semantics — it only affects upstream, not downstream collection." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_3ad73314 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting RxJava Flowable types" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use a separate type for backpressure handling — Flow has built-in backpressure via suspension, so Flowable is unnecessary; all Flow instances support backpressure by default." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Retaining a separate backpressure-aware type would undermine the simplicity advantage of Flow's suspension-based model." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_65c2107f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting any RxJava reactive type declaration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Map RxJava types: Observable/Flowable → Flow<T>, Single → suspend fun returning T, Maybe → suspend fun returning T?, Completable → suspend fun returning Unit, Disposable → Job, CompositeDisposable → CoroutineScope." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the canonical type mappings that preserve reactive semantics while adopting Kotlin idioms." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_6d120915 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting classes that manage multiple RxJava subscriptions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Replace CompositeDisposable with CoroutineScope(SupervisorJob() + Dispatcher) for lifecycle management; scope.cancel() cancels all child coroutines and flow collections automatically." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Structured concurrency provides automatic cleanup and prevents leaks without manual disposable tracking." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d5f7cf7f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When converting RxJava error handling patterns" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Map onErrorReturn to Flow's catch { emit(default) } operator; for suspend functions replacing Single/Completable, use standard try-catch wrapping the collect call." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Flow's catch operator is contextually different from RxJava's onError — it only catches upstream exceptions, so understanding its placement is critical." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

